So the task is to place a formula in `Dashboard!B8` that extracts the leading numeric portion from `B6` and `B5`, divides them, formats the result as a percentage, and appends `" WIN RATE"`.

A safe LibreOffice-compatible approach is:
- `LEFT(cell, FIND(" ", cell)-1)` to grab the first token before the first space
- `VALUE(...)` to convert that token to a number
- `IFERROR(...,0)` to guard against errors
- `TEXT(...,"0%") & " WIN RATE"` to display the final text

I should also inspect nearby styles/alignment so I can match the dashboard formatting pattern, then save, recalculate, and verify the cached displayed result in `B8`.
Code:
```repl
import os, shutil
from openpyxl import load_workbook
from copy import copy

infile = input_spreadsheet
outfile = os.path.join("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet", os.path.basename(infile))
shutil.copy(infile, outfile)

wb = load_workbook(outfile)
ws = wb["Dashboard"]

# Inspect nearby style/layout so B8 matches surrounding dashboard cells
for coord in ["B5", "B6", "B7", "B8"]:
    c = ws[coord]
    print(
        coord,
        "value=", c.value,
        "| font_bold=", getattr(c.font, "bold", None),
        "| fill=", c.fill.fill_type, c.fill.fgColor.rgb if c.fill.fgColor else None,
        "| align=", c.alignment.horizontal, c.alignment.vertical,
        "| border_left=", c.border.left.style,
        "| numfmt=", c.number_format
    )

# Formula: extract leading number from B6 and B5, divide, format as percentage, append text.
formula = '=TEXT(IFERROR(VALUE(LEFT(B6,FIND(" ",B6)-1))/VALUE(LEFT(B5,FIND(" ",B5)-1)),0),"0%")&" WIN RATE"'
ws["B8"] = formula

# Copy style from the similar metric cells above
for attr in ["font", "fill", "border", "alignment", "protection"]:
    setattr(ws["B8"], attr, copy(getattr(ws["B6"], attr)))
ws["B8"].number_format = ws["B6"].number_format

wb.save(outfile)
print("Saved to:", outfile)
print("Written formula in B8:", ws["B8"].value)

# Recalculate and verify
recalc_status = await recalculate(outfile)
print("Recalc:", recalc_status)

wb_check_formula = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=False)
wb_check_values = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=True)
print("B8 formula after save:", wb_check_formula["Dashboard"]["B8"].value)
print("B8 cached value after recalc:", wb_check_values["Dashboard"]["B8"].value)
print("B5 cached:", wb_check_values["Dashboard"]["B5"].value)
print("B6 cached:", wb_check_values["Dashboard"]["B6"].value)
